According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global functional pet food market was valued at USD 24.35 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 25.42 billion in 2026 to USD 31.48 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 4.1% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing steady expansion as pet owners increasingly focus on preventive healthcare, balanced nutrition, and long-term wellness for their companion animals. Functional pet foods fortified with scientifically validated ingredients such as probiotics, prebiotics, omega-3 fatty acids, glucosamine, chondroitin, antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals are becoming an integral part of daily pet diets, supporting digestive health, joint mobility, skin and coat condition, immune function, cognitive development, and healthy weight management.
